data.chText: 朝向；面对；确定方向；使适应
data.enText: to direct sb/sth towards sth; to make or adapt sb/sth for a particular purpose

data.chText: 我们教的学生都是理科方向的。
data.enText: Our students are oriented towards science subjects.

data.chText: 我们经营一个商业性的企业。
data.enText: We run a commercially oriented operation.

data.chText: 他们两人都无意涉足政治。
data.enText: Neither of them is politically oriented (= interested in politics) .

data.chText: 针对职业母亲的需要而制订的政策
data.enText: policies oriented to the needs of working mothers
to find your position in relation to your surroundings

data.chText: 登山者在大雾中很难辨认方向。
data.enText: The mountaineers found it hard to orient themselves in the fog.
to make yourself familiar with a new situation

data.chText: 他经过了一段时间才熟悉新学校的环境。
data.enText: It took him some time to orient himself in his new school.

simple_means.memory_skill: ori 升起；开始 + ent 表名词 →〔太阳〕升起的地方 → 东方

tr: the hemisphere that includes Eurasia and Africa and Australia
adjust to a specific need or market
example: a magazine oriented towards young people
tailor your needs to your surroundings

tr: familiarize (someone) with new surroundings or circumstances
example: The dean of students tries to orient the freshmen

tr: determine one's position with reference to another point
example: We had to orient ourselves in the forest
Orient the house towards the West

value.def: When you orient yourself to a new situation or course of action, you learn about it and prepare to deal with it.

example.ex: You will need the time to orient yourself to your new way of eating.
example.tran: 你还需要一些时间才能适应新的饮食方式。

example.ex: ...orienting students to new ways of thinking about their participation in classroom learning...
example.tran: 使学生熟悉参与课堂教学的新思维方式

example.ex: Anxiety comes from not being able to orient yourself in your own existence.
example.tran: 不能适应生活便会产生焦虑。

value.tran: 使适应，使熟悉（新的环境或行为方式）

value.def: When you orient yourself, you find out exactly where you are and which direction you are facing in.

example.ex: She lay still for a few seconds, trying to orient herself.
example.tran: 她静静地躺了一会儿，试图弄清自己的方位。

value.tran: 使确立方位；使辨清方向

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to rise, to begin 升起；开始
rootsaffixes.title: ori, orig

partsOfSpeech.dec: ab 加强 + orig 升起；开始 + in 进入 + al …的 → 从起源来的 → 原始的
dis 没有 + orient 东方 → 找不到东方 → 迷失方向
ori 升起；开始 + ent 表名词 →〔太阳〕升起的地方 → 东方
orient 东方 + al …的，具有…性质的 → 东方的
orient 东方 + ation 行为，过程，状态，结果 → 向东方 → 定位
orig 升起；开始 + in …素，…精 →〔生命〕开始 → 起源
origin 起源 + al …的，具有…性质的 → 起源的；独创的
origin 起源 + ate 做，造成，使… → 起源
